      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TAP OUT KITTY (1) turned in a plain performance last time when fifth at this track over 520m behind Hey Arnold (30.30) in a Grade 5. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Tough to beat if on-song. MIDNIGHT ARROW (8) was a winner two back when racing on speed but drifted back latest and safely held when 7th and beaten 6 lengths at this track (23.40). Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from six starts. Can figure in the finish. SIDE SHOW BOB (2) turned in a modest effort most recently when sixth at Bulli over 400m behind King Zeal (23.33) in a Grade 5. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Likely to play a prominent role. RUN ROLEX (3) was a close-up placing last start - cannot be ignored.",
